      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is generally not recommended to combine zolpidem with alcohol like red wine. Alcohol can intensify the sedative effects of zolpidem, potentially leading to excessive drowsiness, dizziness, and impaired judgment. For the safest and most effective sleep, it is best to avoid alcohol around the time you take your prescribed medication. Please consult with your doctor or pharmacist about your specific medication plan and dietary habits.",
