      "content": "While a small amount of wine might not cause severe immediate effects, mixing any alcohol with zolpidem still carries risks to your body's functions. Sedatives like zolpidem and alcohol both slow down the central nervous system, which can potentially affect your breathing patterns, even if the initial dose seems small. For the highest safety, it is best to completely separate your wine from your medication. Discussing this specific combination with your prescribing physician is the best way to ensure your safety.",
